parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "obsproc",
"software": [
"grib_util",
"netcdf",
"intel",
"craype",
"cray-mpich",
"cray-pals",
"cfp",
"bufr_dump"
],
"resources": [
"walltime=00:30:00",
"place=vscatter",
"select=1:ncpus=7:mem=12GB"
],
"environment_variables": [
"envir=prod",
"cyc=%CC%",
"DESC=%DESC%",
"JTYP=%JTYP%",
"job=${JTYP}_${cyc}",
"PDY=%PDY%",
"userROOT=/lfs/h2/emc/obsproc/noscrub/$USER",
"obsproc_ver=v1.0",
"obsproc_ver_pckg=v1.0.0",
"bufr_dump_ver=1.0.0",
"obsNET=obsproc",
"PACKAGEROOTpara=/lfs/h1/ops/para/packages",
"HOMEobsproc=${userROOT}/install/obsproc-rmprep",
"VERSION_FILE=${HOMEobsproc}/versions/run.ver",
"SENDECF=NO",
"SENDDBN=NO",
"TANK=$DCOMROOT",
"DATAROOT=/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/${USER}",
"jlogfile=/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/${USER}/${JTYP}.${PDY}.jlogfile",
"COMOUT=${DATAROOT}/CRON/${DESC}/com/${obsNET}/$obsproc_ver/${JTYP}.${PDY}",
"DEBUG_LEVEL=3",
"KEEPDATA=YES"
],
"other_details": [
"The script uses the `JOBSPROC_DUMP_MONITOR` job from the `$HOMEobsproc/jobs` directory.",
"It also defines several environment variables related to the specific job and its dependencies.",
"The script uses the PBS (Portable Batch System) to submit the job.",
"The script relies on specific modules for functionality.",
"The script includes sections for loading modules and checking that they are loaded successfully.",
"The script handles logging and file management depending on whether it's run from cron or manually."
]
}
```
